Several people are using social media to share the lighter side of the recent floods and load-shedding. JOHANNESBURG - South Africans are at their wits end trying to cope with the challenges that have come with the constant rain and rolling blackouts. Eskom has been struggling to keep the lights on since heavy rains started last week. READ: What is Stage 6 load-shedding? On Monday, the power utility announced that it was moving load-shedding to stage 6, sparking anger throughout the country. Meanwhile, the SA Weather Service is warning of more heavy rains and flooding in many parts of the country. Although many South Africans have expressed their anger and frustration, some have taken to social media to poke fun at the situation. This is just one photo doing the rounds as South Africans take the mickey out of load-shedding.